Here are both approaches, using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel to receive data.

## 1. Register the route

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

```csharp
// Approach A â€” string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B â€” pass the full Product object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

## 3. Receive on the ViewModel

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A â€” string parameter arrives as object, call ToString()
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B â€” complex object arrives as-is, just cast it
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire the ViewModel to the page

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **String params** (`?key=value`) â€” values arrive as `object`; call `.ToString()`.
- **Complex objects** â€” use `ShellNavigationQueryParameters`; values arrive as the original type, just cast.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically by Shell on whichever object is the page's `BindingContext`, as long as it implements `IQueryAttributable`.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
